### Step 1: Environment Creation and Dependency Installation
A dedicated Python environment is required to manage the specific dependencies for Stable Diffusion Forge and the Flux architecture.

```bash
# Create a new Conda environment with Python 3.10
conda create -p /path/to/your/env python=3.10 -y
conda activate /path/to/your/env

# Clone the Stable Diffusion Forge repository
git clone [https://github.com/lllyasviel/stable-diffusion-webui-forge.git](https://github.com/lllyasviel/stable-diffusion-webui-forge.git)
cd stable-diffusion-webui-forge
```

### Step 2: Component Acquisition and Path Mapping
Flux. 1-dev requires specific weights and encoders. These must be placed in the respective `models/` subdirectories to be recognized by the Forge backend.

```bash
# 1. Download the FP8 Model Weights (UNet)
python -m huggingface_hub.commands.huggingface_cli download \
  Kijai/flux-fp8 flux1-dev-fp8.safetensors \
  --local-dir models/Stable-diffusion/ \
  --local-dir-use-symlinks False

# 2. Download Text Encoders
python -m huggingface_hub.commands.huggingface_cli download \
  comfyanonymous/flux_text_encoders clip_l.safetensors \
  --local-dir models/text_encoder/

python -m huggingface_hub.commands.huggingface_cli download \
  comfyanonymous/flux_text_encoders t5xxl_fp8_e4m3fn.safetensors \
  --local-dir models/text_encoder/

# 3. Download the Flux VAE
python -m huggingface_hub.commands.huggingface_cli download \
  black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-dev ae.safetensors \
  --local-dir models/VAE/

# 4. Download LoRAs (For stylistic and forensic anomalies)
python -m huggingface_hub.commands.huggingface_cli download \
  XLabs-AI/flux-RealismLora flux_realism_v1.safetensors \
  --local-dir models/Lora/

python -m huggingface_hub.commands.huggingface_cli download \
  ForCu/amateur-photography-v6-flux1-dev amateurphoto-v6.safetensors \
  --local-dir models/Lora/
```

### Step 3: Execution and Memory Optimization
To prevent CUDA Out-Of-Memory (OOM) errors, the server is launched with specific memory-management flags.

```bash
# Launch the server with low-VRAM optimizations
python3 launch.py --listen --xformers --lowvram \
  --cuda-malloc --skip-python-version-check
```
